 February 2015, 14:00\n| Treharris RFC\n| J Jones\n| \n|- bgcolor=#F5FAFF\n| [[British Police|Great Britain Police]]\n| 0 \u2013 38\n| [[Rochdale Mayfield]]\n| Sunday 1 February 2015, 14:30\n| Arthur Miller Stadium, [[Stanningley]]\n| T Grant\n| \n|- bgcolor=#F5FAFF\n| [[Nottingham Outlaws (rugby league team)|Nottingham Outlaws]]\n| 4 \u2013 50\n| [[Blackbrook A.R.L.F.C.]]\n| Saturday 7 February 2015, 13:30\n| [[University of Nottingham|Nottingham University Sports Field]]\n| C Etchells\n| \n|- bgcolor=#F5FAFF\n| [[Featherstone Lions]]\n| 46 \u2013 10\n| [[Queens RLFC]]\n| Saturday 7 February 2015, 13:30\n| The Mill Pond Stadium\n| S Ansell\n| \n|- bgcolor=#F5FAFF\n| [[Shaw Cross Sharks]]\n| 18 \u2013 16\n| [[York|York Acorn]]\n| Saturday 7 February 2015, 14:00\n| Shaw Cross Club\n| S Race\n| \n|- style=\"background:#c1d8ff;\"\n! colspan=12 | Source:<ref>{{cite news |title=Ladbrokes Challenge Cup scoreboard |newspaper=[[Rugby Leaguer & League Express]] |issue=2952 |date=2 February 2015 |page=25 |publisher=League Publications}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Second round==\nThe draw for the second round was made on Monday 2 February at the Oulton Raiders club.  The draw was made by two players who played in the 2014 final. Home teams were drawn by players [[Ryan Hall (rugby league)|Ryan Hall]] of Leeds Rhinos and away teams by [[Oliver Holmes (rugby league)|Oliver Holmes]] of Castleford Tigers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thechallengecup.com/news_video/article/41766/wembley-heroes-to-conduct-ladbrokes |title=Wembley heroes to conduct Ladbrokes Challenge Cup draw |publisher=Rugby Football League |date=2 February 2015 |accessdate=2 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150203120202/http://www.thechallengecup.com/news_video/article/41766/wembley-heroes-to-conduct-ladbrokes |archive-date=3 February 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nFollowing the conclusion of the first round ties; two clubs, Rochdale Mayfield and Hull Dockers, were reported to the Rugby Football League's Operational Rules Tribunal for each fielding an ineligible player.  The Tribunal found both clubs guilty of the offence and disqualified them from the competition.  The teams they defeated in the first round, Great Britain Police and Leigh Miners Rangers, were reinstated into the cup and played in the second round.<ref>{{cite web |title=Two clubs expelled from Challenge Cup |url=http://www.totalrl.com/two-clubs-expelled-from-challenge-cup/ |date=10 February 2015 |accessdate=10 February 2015 |publisher=League Publications |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150211013905/http://www.totalrl.com/two-clubs-expelled-from-challenge-cup/ |archive-date=11 February 2015 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n{| border=1 style=\"border-collapse:collapse; font-size:80%; text-align:center;\" cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 width=100%\n|- bgcolor=#C1D8FF\n!rowspan=2 width=19%|Home\n!rowspan=2 width=6%|Score\n!rowspan=2 width=19%|Away\n!colspan=6|Match Information\n|- bgcolor=#CCCCCC\n!width=17%|Date and Time\n!width=22%|Venue\n!width=10%|Referee\n!width=7%|Attendance\n|- bgcolor=#F5FAFF\n| [[Skirlaugh ARLFC]]\n| 30 \u2013 16\n| [[Royal Navy]]\n| 14 February 2015, 13:00\n| Eastside Community S&S Club\n| J Jones\n| \n|- bgcolor=#F5FAFF\n| [[Siddal RLFC]]\n| 12 \u2013 31\n| [[Featherstone Lions]]\n| 14 February 2015, 13:30\n| [[Brighouse Rangers RFC]]\n| L Moore\n| \n|- bgcolor=#F5FAFF\n| [[Hunslet Warriors]]\n| 8 \u2013 24\n| [[West Hull ARLFC|West Hull]]\n| 14 February 2015, 14:00\n| The Oval\n| B Pearson\n| \n|- bgcolor=#F5FAFF\n| [[Wath Brow Hornets ARLFC|Wath Brow Hornets]]\n| 27 \u2013 12\n| [[Castleford Lock Lane|Lock Lane]]\n| 14 February 2015, 14:00\n| Trumpet Road\n| S Race\n| \n|- bgcolor=#F5FAFF\n| [[Leigh Miners Rangers]]\n| 26 \u2013 18\n| [[Walney Central]]\n| 14 February 2015, 14:00\n| Leigh Miners Welfare S&S Club\n| A Mulligan\n| \n|- bgcolor=#F5FAFF\n| [[Kells RLFC]]\n| 52 \u2013 6\n| [[Blackbrook A.R.L.F.C.]]\n| 14 February 2015, 14:00\n| Old Arrowthw