{"title_page": "List of networking hardware vendors", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=September 2018}}\n[[Networking hardware]] typically refers to equipment facilitating the use of a [[computer networking|computer network]]. Typically, this includes [[router (computing)|router]]s, [[network switch|switches]], [[wireless access point|access point]]s, [[network interface card]]s and other related hardware. This is a   list of notable vendors who produce network hardware.\n\n== Routers ==\n{{Further|Router (computing)}}\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[ADTRAN]]\n* [[Aerohive Networks]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fortune.com/2014/02/14/deals-of-the-day-jos-a-bank-buying-eddie-bauer/|title=Deals of the Day: Jos. A. Bank Buying Eddie Bauer}}</ref><ref name=\"Reference1\">{{Cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2014/02/13/aerohive-networks-files-for-75-million-ipo/|title=Aerohive networks Files for $75 Million IPO}}</ref>\n* [[Alaxala Networks]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=27445525|title=Alaxala Networks|publisher=Bloomberg|date=|accessdate=2017-07-04}}</ref>\n* [[Nokia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2013/1/24/3910528/nokia-q4-2012-financial-report-lumia-sales|title=Nokia finally reports profit after six quarters of losses|first=Aaron|last=Souppouris|date=24 January 2013|publisher=|accessdate=1 June 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Allied Telesis]]\n* [[Alcatel-Lucent|Alcatel]] - Stellar\n* [[Aruba Networks]] - acquired by HPE\n* [[Asus]]\n* [[Avaya]] - acquired [[Nortel]], networking business sold to [[Extreme Networks]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zdnet.com/article/avaya-sells-networking-business-to-extreme-networks-for-100-million/ |title=Avaya sells networking business to Extreme Networks for $100 million |date=March 7, 2017 |accessdate=January 24, 2018 |publisher=ZD Net |author=Natalie Gagliordi}}</ref>\n* [[AVM GmbH|AVM]]\n* [[Brocade Communications Systems|Brocade]] - acquired [[Vyatta]], purchased by [[Broadcom]]<ref name=reuters>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-brocade-commns-m-a-broadcom-idUSKBN12X1A8 |title=Chipmaker Broadcom to buy network gear maker Brocade for $5.5 billion |publisher=reuters.com |date=2016-11-02 |accessdate=2016-11-02}}</ref>\n* [[Billion (company)|Billion Electric]]\n* [[Calix_Inc.|Calix]]\n* [[Cisco Systems]]\n* [[Dell]] - acquired [[Force10]]\n* [[DrayTek]]\n* [[D-Link]]<ref>''[[Bloomberg Businessweek]]''. \"[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/snapshot/snapshot.asp?ticker=2332:TT D-Link Corp].\" Retrieved 11 July 2012.</ref>\n* [[Enterasys Networks|Enterasys]] - acquired by [[Extreme Networks]] in 2013<ref name=\"Fabiaschi\">[http://www.allbusiness.com/company-activities-management/financial-performance/5394406-1.html Enterasys Networks Appoints Michael Fabiaschi President and CEO], [[AllBusiness]], April 26, 2006.</ref>\n* [[Ericsson]] - acquired [[Redback Networks|Redback]]\n* [[Extreme Networks]]\n* [[Fortinet]]\n* [[Hewlett-Packard Enterprise|HPE]] - acquired [[3Com]] and [[Aruba Networks]]\n* [[Huawei]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://e.huawei.com/us/products/enterprise-networking/routers|title=Huawei Routers \u2014 Huawei products|website=Huawei Enterprise}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.computerworld.com/article/2492204/security0/a-better-reason-to-avoid-huawei-routers--code-from-the--90s.html|title=A better reason to avoid Huawei routers: Code from the '90s|first=Jeremy|last=Kirk|website=computerworld.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.zdnet.com/article/huawei-routers-riddled-with-security-flaws-will-not-be-patched/|title=Huawei routers riddled with security flaws won't be patched - ZDNet|first=Zack|last=Whittaker|website=zdnet.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/expert-huawei-routers-are-riddled-with-vulnerabilities/|title=Expert: Huawei routers are riddled with vulnerabilities|date=30 July 2012|website=cnet.com}}</ref>\n* [[Juniper Networks]]\n* [[ELSA Technology|LAN