red by [[Fortinet]]\n* [[MikroTik]]\n* [[Mobileeco]]\n* [[Motorola]]\n* [[NEC]]\n* [[Netgear]]\n* [[Nokia Networks]]\n* [[Open Mesh]] - acquired by Datto\n* [[Proxim]]\n* [[Ruckus Wireless|Ruckus]] - acquired by [[Brocade Communications Systems|Brocade]]; to be acquired by [[Arris International|ARRIS]]\n* [[Siae Microelettronica]]\n* [[Sierra Wireless]]\n* [[Samsung]]\n* [[TP-Link]]\n* [[TRENDnet]]\n* [[Ubiquiti Networks|Ubiquiti]]\n* [[WatchGuard]]\n* [[Xirrus]] - acquired by Cambium Networks\n* [[Yamaha]]\n* [[ZyXEL]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Network interface card ==\n{{Further|Network interface card}}\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Allied Telesis]]\n* [[Broadcom]] (includes former Avago and Emulex)\n* [[Buffalo Technology]]\n* [[Cavium]] (formerly QLogic)\n* [[Chelsio]]\n* [[Cisco]]\n* [[D-Link]]\n* [[Intel]]\n* [[Marvell Technology Group|Marvell]]\n* [[Mellanox]]\n* [[Oracle Corporation]]\n* [[Realtek]]\n* [[TRENDnet]]\n* [[ZyXEL]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Server appliance ==\n{{Further|Server appliance}}\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[aiScaler]]\n* [[ApplianSys]]\n* [[Avaya]]\n* [[NortonLifeLock|Symantec]]\n* [[Cisco]]\n* [[Ciena]]\n* [[Exinda]]\n* [[Expand Networks|Expand]]\n* [[F5 Networks|F5]]\n* [[Hewlett Packard Enterprise|HPE]]\n* [[Infoblox]]\n* [[Lanner Inc]]\n* [[Lotus Foundations]]\n* [[Nortel]]\n* [[Oracle Corporation]]\n* [[PSSC Labs]]\n* [[Radware]]\n* [[Riverbed Technology]]\n* [[Secure64]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Networking hardware companies]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=September 2018}}\n[[Networking hardware]] typically refers to equipment facilitating the use of a [[computer networking|computer network]]. Typically, this includes [[router (computing)|router]]s, [[network switch|switches]], [[wireless access point|access point]]s, [[network interface card]]s and other related hardware. This is a   list of notable vendors who produce network hardware.\n\n== Routers ==\n{{Further|Router (computing)}}\n